PSFTC - Public Schools Foundation of Tippecanoe Co.
September 5 at 9:59 AM ·

17 schools received Rapid Response grants yesterday. I had a great time crisscrossing the county to deliver the good news. Awards totaled $6,577, and all of our allocated money was expended in Round 1. Funding was provided for a wide variety of materials to assist with in person, hybrid and virtual teaching. If you like what we’re doing, show your support by signing up for the virtual Cupcake Run for Public Ed. Event proceeds will be used to fund our spring grant programs.

PSFTC - Public Schools Foundation of Tippecanoe Co.
August 27 at 6:43 PM ·

Are you looking for another good reason to sign up for the virtual Cupcake Run? Of course, the first three good reasons are: 1) it's good for my health to get outdoors and exercise 2) I get cool swag, including a Gigi's cupcake 3) my participation directly helps public school teachers in the community.

How about adding this reason...everyone that is registered for the run will be invited to sign up for a FREE virtual trivia night. It's going to be a ton of fun for the whole family...plus the winning team gets a $50 Arni's gift card!

Plenty of good reasons to sign up today!
https://runsignup.com/Race/IN/WestLafayette/CupcakeRunWalkforPublicEducation

PSFTC - Public Schools Foundation of Tippecanoe Co.
August 24 at 8:10 PM ·

Attention Tippecanoe County public school teachers:

We are excited to announce a new grant initiative in response to the ongoing pandemic. PSFTC will accept Rapid Response grants, effective Monday, August 24, 2020.

Grants up to $200 will be awarded on a rolling basis beginning the week of August 31 and biweekly thereafter until funds run out. This funding is available for resources and supplies to assist with a variety of issues created by the pandemic. The request form is super simple, the timeline is quick, and the followup requirements are very basic.

Click here for the details and to submit your request: http://bit.ly/rr-grants

post_text:
We are looking forward to welcoming students back for the new school year. Families, who prefer the virtual option, need to register by this Friday (11:59 pm July 24). We encourage all in-person and virtual registration this week to help us have accurate numbers that will assist our scheduling and staffing. Returning families register through the Parent Portal.

Families who are new to TSC should call their schools to make an appointment for walk-in registration July 30 and July 31.

Thank you for supporting TSC as we look forward to reopening for the 2020-21 school year.

#tscschools
https://www.tsc.k12.in.us/about/welcome-to-tsc/enroll-now

shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
SROs Are There for You

Tippecanoe County Sheriff's Office
May 18 at 7:51 PM ·

Good evening everyone. This is too good to wait until Wednesday at 3:00 p.m. to post. I would not want to keep this from all of our FRIENDS that long. 😂😂😂

Our SROs are awesome and have been doing some great things for the schools while the buildings have been empty. Some of those things have included playing with items left around the building, a floor cleaning machine ride, and book reading. 😂😂😂😂 They really have been doing great things for our students and staff, and we are very appreciative of the work they do.

We all get a song stuck in our head, quote our favorite movies, or replace song lyrics with our own. Our SROs took one of the greatest TV series of all time, flipped the words to fit our current situation and had some fun doing so. I am sure the recent video they made is going to get you singing and reflecting of the good old days. 😂

Enjoy and remember to.....

Get along, talk nicely to each other, don’t take things that aren’t yours, and call us if you need us. We will be there for you.

https://youtu.be/jxbzv9mJE1U

PSFTC.ORG
Public Schools Foundation of Tippecanoe County | Excellence in Education

PSFTC - Public Schools Foundation of Tippecanoe Co.
December 20, 2019 at 8:45 PM ·

What a great way to finish the semester - hammering and problem solving and working in teams, and hammering some more. "Bee Boxes, Blueberries and Best Friends: Teaching Empathy and Mason Bee Pollination in a Hands-On Way" is such a unique and creative project created by Jessica Ferger and Brittany Bredar for their 4th grade students at Cole Elementary. Such a great example of innovative, hands-on learning!!

Check out the details here: https://psftc.org/grant-program/previous-grant-recipients/

Check out the new School Resource Officer's car!
#tscschools
shared_text:
Tippecanoe County Sheriff's Office
December 13, 2019 at 4:18 PM ·

🎼🎼🎼🎼🎼🎼🎼🎼

SRO Kidwell had her vehicle wrapped
E, I, E, I, O
With the TSC logo here and the TSC logo there
Here a logo there a logo, everywhere a logo logo
SRO Kidwell had her vehicle wrapped
E I E I O
🎼🎼🎼🎼🎼🎼🎼🎼

😂😂😂😂

Good gosh it is Friday and thank goodness for that. Weekend plans? Enjoy. Family gatherings? Show up late, leave early. JK. 😂😂😂😂

Anyway, enjoy the weekend, be safe and it sounds like we have some nasty weather coming which means driving advice will be coming soon. 😉

Take a peek or a gander at the new SRO vehicle pictured below. And, she is parked next to the handicap spot, not in it. Back to singing.

E I E I O....

Get along, talk nice to each other, don't take things that aren't yours, and call us if you need us
